WEBVTT

00:02.044 --> 00:04.330
NARRA TOR:
Previously on Heroes...

00:04.422 --> 00:05.787
This is goodbye.

00:06.424 --> 00:07.584
(EXCLAIMS)

00:07.842 --> 00:09.958
I love you, Dad.

00:10.052 --> 00:11.588
I love you, Claire Bear.

00:11.679 --> 00:14.011
LINDERMAN: I care
about the world.
Ijust want to heal it.

00:14.098 --> 00:15.963
What could you
possibly know
aboutheaHng?

00:17.268 --> 00:18.508
A few things.

00:20.980 --> 00:23.471
MR. BENNET:
The company has developed
a new tracking system

00:23.566 --> 00:25.557
that doesn't
rely on isotopes
and satellites.

00:25.651 --> 00:27.767
It just finds you
wherever you are.

00:27.862 --> 00:30.194
We go to New York,
we wipe out the Walker System.

00:30.281 --> 00:32.488
There's someone
you need to meet.

00:32.575 --> 00:34.190
Molly Walker.

00:34.285 --> 00:35.946
I hear you have
an amazing ability.

00:36.037 --> 00:38.870
They ask me where people are,
and I find them.

00:38.956 --> 00:41.698
THOMPSON:
Molly is the only one
who can stop Sylar.

00:41.792 --> 00:43.293
I must stop you.

00:43.377 --> 00:45.368
Then do it.

00:45.796 --> 00:47.878
Do it! Kill me!

00:47.965 --> 00:50.251
You can't. Now I'm
gonna have to kill you.

00:50.343 --> 00:51.549
Hirol

00:53.471 --> 00:55.302
Your destiny, Nathan,

00:55.389 --> 00:59.883
is to set the course
of history after this
unspeakable act has occurred.

00:59.977 --> 01:02.354
Can you be
the one we need?

01:02.980 --> 01:04.186
That's my boy.

01:04.899 --> 01:06.184
l explode.

01:06.275 --> 01:09.392
l wipe out this whole city.
You, Nathan, everyone.

01:09.487 --> 01:11.102
You explode?

01:11.197 --> 01:12.562
Like a nuclear bomb.

01:16.400 --> 01:16.494
But if I lose it,
you're the only one who can
get close enough to stop me.

01:16.494 --> 01:18.735
Me, Ted.
It doesn't really matter.

01:18.829 --> 01:20.694
But you have to do this.

01:22.500 --> 01:24.206
| just miss my family.

01:24.585 --> 01:26.792
I hope I can make them proud.

01:28.464 --> 01:29.499
Dad!

01:31.050 --> 01:32.381
Claire!

01:33.844 --> 01:35.129
Claire!

01:36.681 --> 01:37.796
What's he doing?

01:37.890 --> 01:39.755
He's absorbing
your ability.

01:41.519 --> 01:43.635
He's gotta make it stop.

01:50.861 --> 01:54.024
Claire, you know
what you have to do.

02:00.371 --> 02:01.656
Do it.

02:08.796 --> 02:10.036
Wait!

02:16.304 --> 02:17.840
I'm okay.

02:30.818 --> 02:32.558
(HIRO SPEAKING JAPANESE)

02:41.537 --> 02:42.572
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

03:34.882 --> 03:35.871
MAN ON PHONE:
Jittetsu Arms.

03:35.966 --> 03:37.046
Hello?

03:37.134 --> 03:40.422
Yes. Do you fix
ancient samurai swords?

03:40.513 --> 03:42.299
Yeah.

03:44.350 --> 03:46.056
My name is Hiro Nakamura,

03:46.143 --> 03:49.226
and the fate of the world
is in your hands.

03:50.773 --> 03:53.480
MR. BENNET:
80 Peter Petrelli
is your uncle.

03:53.734 --> 03:54.769
CLAIRE:
You didn't know that?

03:54.860 --> 03:56.942
There's a lot of things
they never told me.

03:57.029 --> 04:00.613
I thought Peter was
the only person who
could protect me.

04:00.699 --> 04:02.655
And now you're here.

04:07.832 --> 04:10.448
Why did you come
here with them?

04:11.794 --> 04:14.376
The people | used
to work for have
a tracking system.

04:14.463 --> 04:16.624
They can find anybody
anywhere in the world.

04:16.715 --> 04:18.501
We came here
to destroy it.

04:18.592 --> 04:21.834
That's the only way
we can ever start over.

04:21.929 --> 04:24.090
Build a normal life.

04:24.181 --> 04:26.172
Is that even possible?

04:27.226 --> 04:31.219
I mean, I'm not normal
and they're not normal.

04:33.107 --> 04:37.897
Everything that's been
happening to us has been
so monumentally un-normal.

04:38.362 --> 04:39.977
I mean, maybe Peter's right.

04:40.072 --> 04:41.937
Maybe we all have a destiny,

04:42.032 --> 04:45.115
and it's to save
the world together.

04:46.203 --> 04:47.909
| just rode 26
hours from Texas

04:47.997 --> 04:49.658
to take down
the evil bastards
who want me dead,

04:49.748 --> 04:51.124
and you're saying
I should turn around
and go back

04:51.208 --> 04:52.459
because of a painting
that you saw?

04:52.543 --> 04:55.034
Yeah. That and a dream.

04:55.504 --> 04:58.291
He might be nuts, Ted,
but he's not lying.
He believes every word of it.

04:58.382 --> 05:00.668
They'll take out
the tracking system,
then you're gonna be free.

05:00.759 --> 05:03.796
Free? I killed people
with my powers, okay?

05:03.888 --> 05:05.674
I didn't mean to,
but it happened.

05:05.764 --> 05:07.220
And now the FBI thinks
I'm a terrorist.

05:07.308 --> 05:08.844
Yeah, but you're
not a terrorist.

05:08.934 --> 05:10.845
You need to get out of town
before you become one.

05:10.936 --> 05:12.472
There's a town in Nebraska.

05:12.563 --> 05:14.554
Windy Fork,
population 15.

05:14.648 --> 05:16.229
I want you to go there
and wait for me
to contact you.

05:16.317 --> 05:17.477
He gave me directions.

05:17.568 --> 05:18.933
You're sending your
daughter with them?

05:19.028 --> 05:21.610
Claire tells me
she has a destiny.

05:21.697 --> 05:24.484
She stopped Ted from
melting down once before
and saved all our lives.

05:24.575 --> 05:26.190
She could do it again.

05:27.912 --> 05:29.994
She could stop both of you.

05:33.000 --> 05:34.365
You coming?

05:37.254 --> 05:38.460
I'm in.

05:41.675 --> 05:42.926
Me, too.

05:59.777 --> 06:01.517
We can do the photo op
outside the polls.

06:01.612 --> 06:03.273
Yes, Marty. Marty!

06:03.531 --> 06:07.069
I know we're still behind.
That's why every vote counts.

06:10.788 --> 06:12.870
Exit polls have me
five points down.

06:12.957 --> 06:16.040
Oh, I never listen to polls.

06:16.126 --> 06:17.252
(CHUCKLES)

06:17.336 --> 06:18.701
Be ready, Nathan.

06:18.963 --> 06:21.170
Today you will become
a congressman.

06:21.257 --> 06:24.340
In time, you will
lead the country.

06:24.426 --> 06:28.010
As long as I let this city
become a nuclear wasteland.

06:33.519 --> 06:35.350
And let my
brother explode.

06:35.437 --> 06:39.225
You can't stop that.
No one can.

06:39.316 --> 06:41.307
But it's what comes next,

06:41.402 --> 06:45.111
and that is
entirely up to us.

06:46.282 --> 06:48.739
Your father would
be very proud.

06:52.746 --> 06:57.115
Pop would have me
committed for even
considering this nonsense.

06:57.209 --> 06:59.871
Well, clearly, your
mother didn't tell you.

06:59.962 --> 07:01.372
Tell me what?

07:04.800 --> 07:06.756
Your father was
one of us,

07:06.885 --> 07:10.173
someone with great power.

07:10.681 --> 07:14.094
He tried to
make a difference
in the world.

07:14.184 --> 07:17.847
He did all he could,
and when that wasn't enough,

07:19.648 --> 07:21.229
he just gave up.

07:25.070 --> 07:27.356
Your father was weak.

07:33.162 --> 07:35.027
My father was my hero.

07:39.752 --> 07:42.289
I thought you were
gonna see the boys
before they went to school.

07:42.379 --> 07:44.370
They wanted to
wish you good luck.

07:44.465 --> 07:46.171
Oh.

07:47.009 --> 07:48.749
I'm sorry.
I didn't know
you were here.

07:48.844 --> 07:51.756
That's all right.
I'm just on my way out.

07:53.515 --> 07:58.976
Mrs. Petrelli, your
husband is about to become
a very powerful man.

07:59.063 --> 08:02.806
I would like to
give you both a gift

08:02.900 --> 08:06.563
to honor his
forthcoming victory.

08:09.073 --> 08:13.908
Something to make
the days ahead
a little easier.

08:32.763 --> 08:34.754
What is he
talking about?

08:36.225 --> 08:37.681
I don't know.

08:38.352 --> 08:41.515
I can't believe
you let that man
into our house.

08:41.605 --> 08:45.894
Honey, he's my largest
campaign contributor.

08:45.984 --> 08:48.691
He's a thief and a liar
and God knows what else.

08:48.779 --> 08:50.986
And if I win this election,
he'll be the reason.

08:51.073 --> 08:53.439
Why? Because he
gave you money?

08:53.534 --> 08:55.320
Nathan, don't forget
who you are.

08:55.411 --> 08:57.493
I know exactly who I am.

08:58.956 --> 09:02.869
I'm a man who's being
asked to make a hard choice
for the greater good.

09:02.960 --> 09:04.075
And you will.

09:04.169 --> 09:05.909
And you're gonna
do great things,

09:06.004 --> 09:08.290
but you don't have
to sell your soul!

09:11.051 --> 09:12.131
What?

09:12.845 --> 09:14.210
What is it?

09:14.304 --> 09:15.805
Your foot.

09:17.933 --> 09:19.639
lt's moving.

09:19.727 --> 09:21.137
What?

09:23.021 --> 09:24.431
Oh, my God.

09:26.191 --> 09:30.480
Oh, Nathan.
Oh, my God.

09:33.073 --> 09:34.609
(GASPING)

09:35.159 --> 09:37.115
(LAUGHING) Oh, my God!

09:37.202 --> 09:38.817
It's a miracle.

09:45.502 --> 09:47.367
CLAIRE: You know,
I've been thinking
after we save the world,

09:47.463 --> 09:48.418
I may go on patrol.

09:48.505 --> 09:50.120
You know, jumping
in front of bullets

09:50.215 --> 09:53.002
and dragging people
out of burning buildings.

09:53.093 --> 09:54.924
You're not gonna
catch me wearing a cape,

09:55.012 --> 09:57.594
zipping around
with my underwear
outside my pants.

09:57.681 --> 09:58.966
Why do we have
to rent a car?

09:59.057 --> 10:01.309
Can't we just fly
to Nebraska...in a plane?

10:01.393 --> 10:03.179
The FBl's got my face
all over wanted posters.

10:03.312 --> 10:05.769
I wouldn't get very
far in an airport.
