10:05.856 --> 10:07.767
/ can use that
to get his power.

10:07.858 --> 10:09.314
What is it?

10:09.401 --> 10:10.777
lt's Sylar.

10:10.861 --> 10:11.976
He's here.
He's watching us.

10:12.070 --> 10:13.810
Right now?

10:13.906 --> 10:15.112
He knows what
Ted can do.

10:15.199 --> 10:17.281
We need to
get off the streets.

10:18.535 --> 10:20.196
Who's Sylar?

10:24.666 --> 10:26.577
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

10:50.234 --> 10:52.099
Would have been nice
to have Heidi
for the photo op.

10:52.194 --> 10:53.684
Something happened
back at the house.

10:53.779 --> 10:54.814
Is she all right?

10:54.905 --> 10:56.691
Yeah. She's fine.

10:56.907 --> 10:58.989
She's better
than fine, actually.

10:59.243 --> 11:01.609
Nathan Petrelli! Nathan!

11:01.703 --> 11:03.113
We'll make an announcement
after the election.

11:03.205 --> 11:04.695
HIRO: Nathan!
What's going on?

11:04.790 --> 11:06.155
Miracles, Marty.

11:06.250 --> 11:07.956
Nathan Petrelli,
Nathan!

11:08.043 --> 11:09.624
Nathan Petrelli!

11:10.504 --> 11:12.244
HIRO: No, I need
to speak to Nathan.

11:12.339 --> 11:14.546
It's all right.
Mr. Hiro, how are you?

11:14.633 --> 11:16.715
Fine. Thank you
very much.

11:17.427 --> 11:19.213
We are trying to
stop a bad thing.

11:19.304 --> 11:20.919
(SHUSHING)

11:22.432 --> 11:24.718
(WHISPERING)
The bomb. Big boom.

11:24.810 --> 11:27.927
You must help,
or bad future will come.

11:29.064 --> 11:30.019
Bad future?

11:30.107 --> 11:33.599
Yes, we went there,
but I was already dead.

11:34.820 --> 11:39.189
You become
a bad person, Nathan.

11:41.702 --> 11:43.567
But you can come
with us now,

11:43.662 --> 11:45.698
help us stop
a bomb together.

11:46.623 --> 11:48.875
I'm sorry, Hiro.

11:48.959 --> 11:50.950
I can't stop it.

11:54.464 --> 11:55.965
Nobody can.

11:59.344 --> 12:00.925
It's a pleasure
to see you again.

12:01.638 --> 12:03.014
Thanks for your support.

12:03.891 --> 12:06.553
(REPORTERS CLAMORING)

12:07.185 --> 12:08.971
You already bad guy.

12:10.939 --> 12:12.440
You are villain!

12:12.941 --> 12:13.930
Villain!

12:15.152 --> 12:16.642
Thank you all.

12:18.655 --> 12:20.520
Villain!

12:20.616 --> 12:21.822
D.L.: That's Petrelli?

12:21.909 --> 12:23.194
Yep.

12:23.285 --> 12:25.446
I don't see Micah
or Linderman.

12:25.537 --> 12:26.993
We know they're in town.

12:27.497 --> 12:29.033
Nathan can tell us where.

12:31.126 --> 12:33.333
He'll never
see us coming.

12:34.171 --> 12:36.878
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

12:57.819 --> 12:58.808
Hiro!

12:59.696 --> 13:01.732
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

13:08.789 --> 13:10.370
Mr. Claremont?

13:11.625 --> 13:13.866
It's me. Hiro Nakamura.

13:13.961 --> 13:15.451
I spoke to you
on the phone.

13:17.381 --> 13:19.497
About my problem.

13:28.850 --> 13:30.181
My God.

13:31.645 --> 13:33.010
The Kensei.

13:34.982 --> 13:36.768
What happened?

13:36.858 --> 13:38.394
It got cold.

13:38.485 --> 13:41.192
Frozen. Then snap.

13:42.155 --> 13:43.736
Can you fix it?

13:44.783 --> 13:46.114
Depends

13:47.744 --> 13:48.904
on him.

13:56.420 --> 13:59.253
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

14:08.849 --> 14:11.010
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

14:55.312 --> 14:56.301
Hiro!

15:05.781 --> 15:07.567
l have a cousin
who eats like you.

15:07.657 --> 15:09.363
He's huge.

15:09.826 --> 15:11.077
So am I.

15:12.704 --> 15:15.867
You said you like comic books,
so I bought you a stack.

15:18.043 --> 15:19.533
Anything good?

15:21.004 --> 15:24.041
The original Silver Surfer
number one?

15:24.674 --> 15:26.710
This must have
cost you a fortune!

15:26.802 --> 15:28.292
Yeah.

15:28.804 --> 15:31.090
You're nice,
even when you're scary.

15:31.223 --> 15:32.554
(CHUCKLES)

15:33.475 --> 15:36.433
| just don't understand
why you're working
for such a bad guy.

15:36.520 --> 15:38.681
You could use your power
to be a hero.

15:38.772 --> 15:40.808
Oh, okay.

15:40.899 --> 15:44.357
No, you're just too
young to see how
much the world sucks,

15:45.153 --> 15:49.237
how people can be so mean
to each other just because
of where they were born

15:50.117 --> 15:52.073
or what they look like.

15:52.536 --> 15:53.525
(CHUCKLES)

15:56.456 --> 15:59.038
Mr. Linderman's gonna
change all that.

16:01.837 --> 16:04.453
He's gonna heal the world.

16:04.548 --> 16:07.039
I didn't know
it was sick.

16:08.510 --> 16:10.250
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

16:12.597 --> 16:14.303
Candice.
Mr. Linderman.

16:14.391 --> 16:15.722
How are you?
Good.

16:15.809 --> 16:17.470
And how is our boy?

16:17.561 --> 16:18.892
Good, sir.

16:20.564 --> 16:21.895
I wanna see my mom.

16:21.982 --> 16:24.439
After today,
you can go home.

16:24.568 --> 16:25.774
I don't believe you.

16:25.861 --> 16:29.649
I'm sure other grownups
talk down to you, Micah.

16:29.739 --> 16:32.071
I'm not gonna
make that mistake.

16:32.159 --> 16:34.525
I'm gonna look you
straight in the eye

16:34.786 --> 16:37.118
and tell you
one simple truth.

16:38.290 --> 16:43.910
What you do here
today with your
incredible ability

16:44.004 --> 16:46.541
is going to
save many lives.

16:51.595 --> 16:53.460
What do you want me to do?

16:53.555 --> 16:55.341
What comes naturally.

16:55.432 --> 16:57.548
Talking to machines.

16:57.642 --> 16:59.849
And after that,
you'll take me home?

16:59.936 --> 17:02.222
I'll tell you what.
I'll do better than that.

17:02.314 --> 17:06.353
You do as you're told,
and I'll make sure that
you and your parents

17:06.443 --> 17:10.436
have enough money
to live happily ever after.

17:13.909 --> 17:16.070
So this guy Sylar,
he kills people like us?

17:16.161 --> 17:17.446
Yeah, to take
what we can do.

17:17.537 --> 17:18.617
How does he
manage that?

17:18.705 --> 17:20.445
He rips your head open.

17:20.540 --> 17:23.202
Then I say we stick
with the plan,
get out of the city.

17:23.293 --> 17:24.248
(TIRES SQUEALING)

17:24.336 --> 17:25.667
(SIRENS BLARING)

17:26.630 --> 17:27.995
Get out of here. Go!

17:28.131 --> 17:29.871
Federal agents.
On your knees!
Get out of here, Claire.

17:29.966 --> 17:31.922
Now! Now!

17:32.469 --> 17:33.458
(GASPS)

17:33.929 --> 17:35.260
Let's go!

17:36.097 --> 17:38.088
There were two others!
Find them.

17:38.516 --> 17:39.926
You're under arrest.

17:40.018 --> 17:41.474
Agent Hanson?

17:41.561 --> 17:43.643
I've been chasing you
all across the country, Ted.

17:43.730 --> 17:45.231
You know
I'm not a terrorist.

17:45.315 --> 17:46.395
Do I?

17:46.483 --> 17:48.849
You blew up
a van full of federal
agents in Los Angeles.

17:48.944 --> 17:50.605
But I didn't mean
to hurt anybody.

17:50.695 --> 17:53.687
Good. Your next stop,
Guantanamo Bay.

17:53.782 --> 17:56.774
Look, I'm gonna
need a concrete cell
lined with lead.

17:56.868 --> 17:59.154
So everyone is safe!

18:01.122 --> 18:03.659
We got him, thanks
to your tip, Mister...

18:03.750 --> 18:06.036
Mendez. lsaac Mendez.

18:06.670 --> 18:08.911
I thought I recognized
Sprague from his picture
in the post office.

18:09.005 --> 18:10.745
I knew it was
my duty to call,

18:10.840 --> 18:12.546
especially with it
being election day.

18:12.634 --> 18:15.797
Well, you helped us
capture a very
dangerous man.

18:15.887 --> 18:18.003
Most people wouldn't
take the risk.

18:18.098 --> 18:20.510
I'm not most people.

18:27.023 --> 18:28.604
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

18:38.368 --> 18:39.778
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

19:51.816 --> 19:52.805
Hiro.

20:48.206 --> 20:50.868
Welcome, Miss Baker.

20:50.959 --> 20:54.042
Do you mind if I take
my son into the
voting booth with me?

20:54.129 --> 20:56.415
I'm trying to
teach him about
democracy in action.

20:56.506 --> 20:59.839
Oh, what a lovely
thought. Follow me.

21:01.845 --> 21:04.632
I've been thinking
about how you make
yourself look like that.

21:04.722 --> 21:07.304
You must bend
light or something.

21:07.392 --> 21:10.475
How do you know
this isn't the real me?

21:10.770 --> 21:12.351
(CHUCKUNG)

21:14.232 --> 21:15.563
(CHUCKUNG)

21:18.111 --> 21:20.602
Okay, Micah,
it's time to boot up.

21:20.697 --> 21:22.688
What do you
want me to do?

21:22.949 --> 21:24.905
You can tell
computers what to do.

21:24.993 --> 21:27.951
So I want you to
tell this one and
all the others here

21:28.037 --> 21:30.904
to vote for Nathan Petrelli.

21:36.379 --> 21:40.167
After this, we do
the same thing in
12 other precincts.

21:40.258 --> 21:41.919
We don't have to go
anywhere else.

21:42.010 --> 21:43.500
It says that they're
all networked.

21:43.595 --> 21:46.462
So from here,
I can change every
one in the city.

21:47.724 --> 21:48.759
Yeah.

21:48.850 --> 21:51.842
How many votes
does your boss
want him to win by?

21:51.936 --> 21:53.722
Make it a landslide.

22:02.238 --> 22:04.399
(COMPUTER BUZZING)

22:05.450 --> 22:06.439
(GASPS)

22:08.411 --> 22:09.617
(SIGHS)

22:09.787 --> 22:11.743
Can I go home now?

22:27.430 --> 22:30.172
